urls.title: PACO RABANNE’S ‘12 UNWEARABLE’ NFTs | Selfridges | Charli Cohen - Paco Rabanne | Foundation Vasarely
urls.description: For his debut couture collection in 1966, Paco Rabanne presented ‘12 unwearable dresses in contemporary materials’. Now, the brand is pushing the concept of ‘unwearable’ further – uniting the past, present and future by creating 12 NFT dresses based on some of its most conceptual couture designs from the past seven decades. This 360 project re-transcribes the it through technological innovation, bringing together the great traditions of the past and the limitless potential of the future. Owners of exclusive 1/1 NFTs will receive an exclusive invitation to the Paris atelier, where Julien Dossena and the French artisans who made the original heritage pieces will collaborate to create a custom physical version of the archive NFT design – made to measure to the owner’s requirements. This unique experience will also include a VIP invite to the next Paco Rabanne show, as a special guest of the fashion house.
